      {
        "position": 5,
        "title": "Great fit and quality, but hood design is awkward and it didn’t reduce my dog’s anxiety",
        "text": "I ordered this calming hoodie in a size small, color dark green, for my 13 pound dog, and it fits perfectly. I followed the size chart and found it to be accurate. The fabric is thick, smooth, and well made, and the snug fit (except around the neck) seems intentional. The strong, high quality Velcro allows for a very secure, almost custom fit, and it holds so well that it can be difficult to open when aligned just right. The dark green is more of a hunter green, and it looks great on him.I don’t love the hood design. The drawstring runs straight from the back of the neck to the front, creating a loose loop that hangs between his eyes when tightened. It doesn’t fit as neatly as the rest of the shirt, so I usually roll it down and use it like a thick collar.My dog isn’t anxious about thunder or fireworks, but he reacts strongly to other dogs, especially those passing our home or during walks. Unfortunately, the hoodie didn’t help with this type of anxiety. He still barks excessively and can irritate his throat from barking for such an extended period of time, long after the other dogs are gone.Even so, he enjoys wearing the hoodie. It’s durable, comfortable, and very pleasant to pet him while he’s wearing it, thanks to the smooth fabric.",
